22:
He reveals the deep and hidden things;
he knows what is in the darkness,
and light dwells with him.

16:
Lord, in keeping with all your righteous acts, may your anger and wrath
 turn away from your city Jerusalem, your holy mountain;
 for because of our sins and the iniquities of our ancestors, Jerusalem and your people have become an object of ridicule to all those around us.

21:
while I was praying, Gabriel,
 the man I had seen in the first vision,
 reached me in my extreme weariness, about the time of the evening offering.
